{"parse":{"title":"Echetlus","pageid":10497760,"revid":810510438,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Echetlaeus</b> (<a href=\"/wiki/Greek_language\" title=\"Greek language\">Greek</a>: <span lang=\"el\">\u1f18\u03c7\u03b5\u03c4\u03bb\u03b1\u1fd6\u03bf\u03c2</span>) or <b>Echetlus</b> (<a href=\"/wiki/Greek_language\" title=\"Greek language\">Greek</a>: <span lang=\"el\">\u1f1c\u03c7\u03b5\u03c4\u03bb\u03bf\u03c2</span>) was an <a href=\"/wiki/Ancient_Athens\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ancient Athens\">ancient Athenian</a> mythical hero of the  <a href=\"/wiki/Battle_of_Marathon\" title=\"Battle of Marathon\">Battle of Marathon</a> with the <a href=\"/wiki/Achaemenid_Empire\" title=\"Achaemenid Empire\">Persians of the Achaemenid Empire</a>. The latter name was also the name of a hero of ancient Thebes.\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#The_hero_of_the_Athenians\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">The hero of the Athenians</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Echetlus_of_Thebes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Echetlus of Thebes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Source\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Source</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"The_hero_of_the_Athenians\">The hero of the Athenians</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Echetlus&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: The hero of the Athenians\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>The following tradition was current in ancient Athens after the Battle of Marathon. \n</p><p>During the battle, a man appeared among the Athenians, who resembled a rustic, and slew many of the Persians with his plough. After the battle, he disappeared. When the Athenians searched for him, they couldn't find him anywhere.When they consulted the <a href=\"/wiki/Oracle\" title=\"Oracle\">oracle</a>, they were commanded to worship the hero Echetlaeus, that is the hero with the <i>echetlon</i>, or <a href=\"/wiki/Ploughshare\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Ploughshare\">ploughshare</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:AgoraAthens5thcentury.png\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/80/AgoraAthens5thcentury.png/220px-AgoraAthens5thcentury.png\" width=\"220\" height=\"196\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/80/AgoraAthens5thcentury.png/330px-AgoraAthens5thcentury.png 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/80/AgoraAthens5thcentury.png/440px-AgoraAthens5thcentury.png 2x\" data-file-width=\"808\" data-file-height=\"720\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:AgoraAthens5thcentury.png\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Plan showing the major buildings of the Agora; the Stoa Poikile is number 20</div></div></div>\n<p>This Echetlus was depicted in the painting which represented the Battle of Marathon in the <a href=\"/wiki/Stoa_Poikile\" title=\"Stoa Poikile\">Stoa Poikile</a> (Painted Porch), erected during the 5th century BC and located in the <a href=\"/wiki/Ancient_Agora_of_Athens\" title=\"Ancient Agora of Athens\">Ancient Agora of Athens</a>. The Stoa Poikile was one of the most famous sites in ancient Athens, due to its display of war-related paintings and loot.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Echetlus_of_Thebes\">Echetlus of Thebes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Echetlus&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Echetlus of Thebes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In addition, in the play <i><a href=\"/wiki/Seven_Against_Thebes\" title=\"Seven Against Thebes\">Seven Against Thebes</a></i>, <b>Echetlus</b> is the name of one of the defenders of <a href=\"/wiki/Thebes,_Greece\" title=\"Thebes, Greece\">Thebes</a>. He is killed when the seven attacked the city.<sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Echetlus&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Pausanias 1.32.5</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-2\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Statius, Thebaid, 10.296 <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external autonumber\" href=\"http://www.theoi.com/Text/StatiusThebaid10.html\">[1]</a></span>\n</li>\n</ol></div>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Source\">Source</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Echetlus&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" 